          </div><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/person/3186">http://syriaca.org/person/3186</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Personal Information</h3><h4>Name variant(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Abraham II, Archimandrite of
                                <span class="tei-placeName"> the <span class="tei-placeName">Convent of John
                                    Urtaya</span> in <span class="tei-placeName">Amida</span></span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/10510-82" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Abraham
                                    II</span> was male. <a href="/10510-83" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Abraham
                                    II</span> was the archimandrite of <span class="tei-placeName"> the <span class="tei-placeName">Convent of John
                                        Urtaya</span> in <span class="tei-placeName">Amida</span></span> <a href="/10510-84" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Abraham
                                    II</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName"> Urtaye in the district of
                                    Anzetene</span>. <a href="/10510-96" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Anonymi 3675 had enmity for Abraham. <a href="/10510-109" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Abraham was a monastic authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-85" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Abraham had ecclesiastical authority over Anonymous 3673. <a href="/10510-97" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">Anonymi
                            3673 of the Convent of John Urtaya disliked Abraham II's
                            appointment of Abraham
                                III as his successor, believing him to be a lowly
                            peasant. Sixty
                                monks left the convent.  <a href="/10510-107" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Abraham II
                            succeeded Abraham
                                I as the head of the convent.  <a href="/10510-81" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> As Abraham
                                II's reputation as an excellent leader grew, King Zeno gifted him
                            with a village in  Narda
                                in the district of 
                                    Ingelene  <a href="/10510-86" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Abraham II
                            gave half of the land that he received from King Zeno to
                                the
                                brothers of the Monastery of Zuknin.
                         <a href="/10510-90" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Abraham II
                            was promoted to the bishopric in Urtaye in the district of
                                Anzetene.  <a href="/10510-95" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Anonymi 3673
                            of the Convent of John
                                Urtaya urged Bishop Abraham to
                            appoint a new head. Abraham chose Abraham the
                            Shepherd, who was formerly a shepherd from the Village of Thella d
                                Mikhana.  <a href="/10510-98" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Abraham the
                                Shepherd succeeded Abraham II as head of
                                the Convent of John
                                Urtaya.  <a href="/10510-99" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
